go_data.justification: MOR28 is an olfactory receptor gene, suggesting it enables olfactory receptor activity.

go_data.term: detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of smell
go_data.justification: As an olfactory receptor, MOR28 is involved in detecting chemical stimuli for sensory perception of smell.
MOR28 is expressed in the olfactory epithelium, specifically in zone 4.
